      • checkAttributeValue

        public java.lang.Object checkAttributeValue(A rAttribute,
                                            java.lang.Object rValue)
                                     throws StorageException
        Implemented to perform value conversions to some standard datatypes. This especially includes string parsing and primitive datatype wrapping. The supported string conversions are
        • Datatype Class: Class.forName(String)
        • Datatype RelationType: RelationType.valueOf(String)
        • Enums: Enum.valueOf(Class, String) with handling of HasOrder prefixes
        • Datatype Period: Period.valueOf(String)
        • Datatype Collection: Conversions.parseCollection(String, Class, Class, boolean)
        • Datatype Map: Conversions.parseMap(String, Class, Class, Class, boolean)
        • Any datatype that has either a constructor with a String parameter or a valueOf(String) method.
        Specified by:
        checkAttributeValue in interface StorageMapping<T,A extends org.obrel.core.Relatable,C extends StorageMapping<?,A,?>>
        Parameters:
        rAttribute - The attribute descriptor
        rValue - The attribute value to be checked (may be NULL)
        Returns:
        The attribute value, converted if necessary
        Throws:
        StorageException - If accessing storage data for a conversion fails
        See Also:
        StorageMapping.checkAttributeValue(Relatable, Object)

      • mapValue

        public java.lang.Object mapValue(A rAttribute,
                                 java.lang.Object rValue)
                          throws StorageException
        Base implementation that converts collections and maps to strings by invoking Conversions.asString(Object). All other values will be returned unchanged.
        Specified by:
        mapValue in interface StorageMapping<T,A extends org.obrel.core.Relatable,C extends StorageMapping<?,A,?>>
        Parameters:
        rAttribute - The descriptor of the attribute to map
        rValue - The value to be mapped (may be NULL)
        Returns:
        The mapped value
        Throws:
        StorageException - Implementations may throw an storage exception if they cannot map a value or need to perform other storage operations for the mapping
        See Also:
        StorageMapping.mapValue(Relatable, Object)
